{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771236230,"nonce":"SxIj8lF5e29i9TLDFk9OmckWsj8=","title":"Email change needs proper verification flow","message":"When a user changes their email address, the change should not take effect immediately. Required flow:\n\n1. User requests email change (must enter current password to confirm)\n2. Verification email sent to the NEW address\n3. Old email stays valid until the new one is confirmed\n4. Optionally notify the old address about the change request\n\nThis likely requires enabling Devise's :confirmable module (with reconfirmable) or a custom implementation. Currently :confirmable is disabled on the User model.","files":null}]}